{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-001", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 1, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.1", "sort_key": "078.001", "text_original": "There is nothing in the world more soft and weak than water, and yet for attacking things that are firm and strong there is nothing that can take precedence of it;", "text_normalized": "There is nothing in the world more soft and weak than water, and yet for attacking things that are firm and strong there is nothing that can take precedence of it;", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-002", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 2, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.2", "sort_key": "078.002", "text_original": "- for there is nothing (so effectual) for which it can be changed.", "text_normalized": "- for there is nothing (so effectual) for which it can be changed.", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-003", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 3, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.3", "sort_key": "078.003", "text_original": "Every one in the world knows that the soft overcomes the hard, and the weak the strong, but no one is able to carry it out in practice.", "text_normalized": "Every one in the world knows that the soft overcomes the hard, and the weak the strong, but no one is able to carry it out in practice.", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-004", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 4, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.4", "sort_key": "078.004", "text_original": "Therefore a sage has said,", "text_normalized": "Therefore a sage has said,", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-005", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 5, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.5", "sort_key": "078.005", "text_original": "'He who accepts his state's reproach,", "text_normalized": "'He who accepts his state's reproach,", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-006", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 6, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.6", "sort_key": "078.006", "text_original": "Is hailed therefore its altars' lord;", "text_normalized": "Is hailed therefore its altars' lord;", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-007", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 7, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.7", "sort_key": "078.007", "text_original": "To him who bears men's direful woes", "text_normalized": "To him who bears men's direful woes", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-008", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 8, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.8", "sort_key": "078.008", "text_original": "They all the name of King accord.'", "text_normalized": "They all the name of King accord.'", "notes": ""}
{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891__seg-009", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-078", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-078__legge-chinesenotes-1891", "language": "en", "segment_type": "sentence", "segment_order": 9, "canonical_ref": "老子 78.9", "sort_key": "078.009", "text_original": "Words that are strictly true seem to be paradoxical.", "text_normalized": "Words that are strictly true seem to be paradoxical.", "notes": ""}
